message.content:
To calculate the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio, the formula is:

\[
\text{Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio} = \frac{\text{Net Credit Sales}}{\text{Average Accounts Receivable}}
\]

From the data:
- Net Credit Sales = Total Revenue (assuming all sales are on credit) = 5,760,023.09
- Accounts Receivable at beginning (Initial_amount) = 0.00 (as per balance sheet at 2023-12-31)
- Accounts Receivable at end (End_amount) = 1,454,443.80 (as per balance sheet at 2024-01-28)

Since initial is zero, average accounts receivable = (0 + 1,454,443.80) / 2 = 727,221.90

Calculating turnover ratio:

\[
\frac{5,760,023.09}{727,221.90} \approx 7.92
\]

Hence, the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio is approximately 7.92.
